 -- Function: np_eye (N) / NP_EYE (N, M) / NP_EYE (N, M, DTYPE)
     Create an identity matrix.

     Returns an ‘n’ x ‘n’ identity matrix (ones on the diagonal, zeros
     elsewhere).  An optional second argument ‘m’ creates an ‘n’ x ‘m’
     rectangular identity matrix.  Pass ‘complex’ as the last argument
     to create a complex array.

     Calling forms:

        • ‘np_eye(n)’ - square identity matrix
        • ‘np_eye(n, m)’ - rectangular identity matrix
        • ‘np_eye(n, m, complex)’ - complex identity matrix

