 -- Function: np_trapz (Y) / NP_TRAPZ (Y, X)
     Trapezoidal numerical integration of a 1D ndarray.

     Without an ‘x’ argument, uses unit spacing (dx = 1).  With an ‘x’
     argument, uses the spacing defined by the ‘x’ array.  Both ‘y’ and
     ‘x’ must be 1D ndarrays of the same length.  Returns a scalar.

     Calling forms:

        • ‘np_trapz(y)’ - integrate with unit spacing
        • ‘np_trapz(y, x)’ - integrate with variable spacing defined by
          x

* Menu:

     * Examples: Examples 94.


File: numerics.info,  Node: Examples 94,  Next: Examples 95,  Prev: Examples 93,  Up: Image representation

1.3.3.19 Examples
.................

(%i1) /* Unit spacing: integral of [1, 2, 3] = 0.5*(1+2) + 0.5*(2+3) = 4 */
      np_trapz(ndarray([1, 2, 3], [3]));
(%o1)                          4.0
(%i2) /* Variable spacing: y=x^2 on [0,1,2] */
      x : ndarray([0, 1, 2], [3]);
(%o2)            ndarray([3], DOUBLE-FLOAT)
(%i3) y : ndarray([0, 1, 4], [3]);
(%o3)            ndarray([3], DOUBLE-FLOAT)
