 -- Function: np_eig (A)
     Eigendecomposition.

     Computes eigenvalues and eigenvectors of a square matrix.  Returns
     a Maxima list ‘[eigenvalues, eigenvectors]’ where ‘eigenvalues’ is
     a 1D ndarray and ‘eigenvectors’ is a 2D ndarray whose columns are
     the eigenvectors.

     When eigenvalues have non-negligible imaginary parts (e.g. rotation
     matrices, non-symmetric matrices), the returned ndarrays use
     ‘complex-double-float’ dtype.  When all eigenvalues are real,
     returns ‘double-float’ ndarrays.

