 -- Function: np_qr (A)
     QR decomposition.  Works for any m-by-n matrix.  Supports complex
     arrays.

     Decomposes ‘a’ into an orthogonal (or unitary for complex) matrix Q
     and an upper triangular (or upper trapezoidal) matrix R such that A
     = Q * R. Returns a Maxima list ‘[Q, R]’.  For tall/square matrices
     (m >= n), uses LAPACK. For wide matrices (m < n), uses Householder
     reflections.

